devdoc.details: Handles receiving and resolving price requests via a commit-reveal voting scheme.

addMember(uint256,address).details: Reverts if `roleId` does not represent an initialized, shared role or if the caller is not a member of the managing role for `roleId`.

params._gatPercentage: percentage of the total token supply that must be used in a vote to create a valid price resolution.
params._isTest: whether this contract is being constructed for the purpose of running automated tests.
params.phaseLength: length of the commit and reveal phases in seconds.

getMember(uint256).details: Reverts if `roleId` does not represent an initialized, exclusive role.

getMessage(address,bytes32).details: To decrypt messages (this requires access to the recipient's private keys), use the decryptMessage() function in common/Crypto.js.

getPublicKey(address,bytes32).details: Senders may need this public key to encrypt messages that only the `recipient` can read. If the public key is communicated offchain, this field may be left empty.

hasRevealedVote(bytes32,uint256).details: If the price request was resolved in a previous round, this function will return `false` even if the caller did reveal a vote.

holdsRole(uint256,address).details: Reverts if roleId does not correspond to an initialized role.

removeMember(uint256,address).details: Reverts if `roleId` does not represent an initialized, shared role or if the caller is not a member of the managing role for `roleId`.

resetMember(uint256,address).details: Reverts if the caller is not a member of the managing role for `roleId` or if `roleId` is not an initialized, exclusive role.

sendMessage(address,bytes32,bytes).details: To construct an encrypted message, use the encryptMessage() in common/Crypto.js. The public key for the recipient can be obtained using the getPublicKey() method.

setCurrentTime(uint256).details: Will revert if not running in test mode.

setInflationRate((uint256)).details: This method is public because calldata structs are not currently supported by solidity.

setPublicKey(bytes,bytes32).details: Note: setting the public key is optional - if the publicKey is communicated or can be derived offchain by the sender, there is no need to set it here. Because there are no specific requirements for the publicKey, there is also no verification of its validity other than its length.

devdoc.title: Voting system for Oracle.

addAuthorizedSender(address).notice: Authorizes `sender` to send messages to the caller.

addSupportedIdentifier(bytes32).notice: Adds the provided identifier as a supported identifier.

getCurrentTime().notice: Gets the current time. Will return the last time set in `setCurrentTime` if running in test mode. Otherwise, it will return the block timestamp.

getMember(uint256).notice: Gets the current holder of the exclusive role, `roleId`.

getMessage(address,bytes32).notice: Gets the current stored message corresponding to `recipient` and `topicHash`.

getPublicKey(address,bytes32).notice: Gets the stored public key for a particular `recipient` and `topicHash`. Return value will be 0 length if no public key has been set.

hasRevealedVote(bytes32,uint256).notice: Whether the caller has a revealed vote for the current round for an (identifier, time).

holdsRole(uint256,address).notice: Whether `memberToCheck` is a member of roleId.

isAuthorizedSender(address,address).notice: Returns true if the `sender` is authorized to send to the `recipient`.

removeAuthorizedSender(address).notice: Revokes `sender`'s authorization to send messages to the caller.

resetMember(uint256,address).notice: Changes the exclusive role holder of `roleId` to `newMember`.

sendMessage(address,bytes32,bytes).notice: Sends `message` to `recipient_` categorized by a particular `topicHash`. This will overwrite any previous messages sent to this `recipient` with this `topicHash`.

setInflationRate((uint256)).notice: Resets the inflation rate. Note: this change only applies to rounds that have not yet begun.

setPublicKey(bytes,bytes32).notice: Sets the public key for this caller and topicHash.
